androidx.tvprovider.media.tv

Class TvContractCompat

  • java.lang.Object
    • androidx.tvprovider.media.tv.TvContractCompat

  • public final class TvContractCompat
extends java.lang.Object
    The contract between the TV provider and applications. Contains definitions for the supported URIs and columns.

    Overview

    TvContract defines a basic database of TV content metadata such as channel and program information. The information is stored in TvContractCompat.Channels and TvContractCompat.Programs tables.

    • A row in the TvContractCompat.Channels table represents information about a TV channel. The data format can vary greatly from standard to standard or according to service provider, thus the columns here are mostly comprised of basic entities that are usually seen to users regardless of standard such as channel number and name.
    • A row in the TvContractCompat.Programs table represents a set of data describing a TV program such as program title and start time.

      • ACTION_CHANNEL_BROWSABLE_REQUESTED

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_CHANNEL_BROWSABLE_REQUESTED
        Broadcast Action: sent when an application requests the system to make the given channel browsable. The operation is performed in the background without user interaction. This is only relevant to channels with TvContractCompat.Channels.TYPE_PREVIEW type.

        The intent must contain the following bundle parameters:

        • EXTRA_CHANNEL_ID: ID for the TvContractCompat.Channels.TYPE_PREVIEW channel as a long integer.
        • EXTRA_PACKAGE_NAME: the package name of the requesting application.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_REQUEST_CHANNEL_BROWSABLE

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_REQUEST_CHANNEL_BROWSABLE
        Activity Action: sent by an application telling the system to make the given channel browsable with user interaction. The system may show UI to ask user to approve the channel. This is only relevant to channels with TvContractCompat.Channels.TYPE_PREVIEW type. Use Activity#startActivityForResult to get the result of the request.

        The intent must contain the following bundle parameters:

        • EXTRA_CHANNEL_ID: ID for the TvContractCompat.Channels.TYPE_PREVIEW channel as a long integer.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_PREVIEW_PROGRAM_BROWSABLE_DISABLED

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_PREVIEW_PROGRAM_BROWSABLE_DISABLED
        Broadcast Action: sent by the system to tell the target TV input that one of its preview program's browsable state is disabled, i.e., it will no longer be shown to users, which, for example, might be a result of users' interaction with UI. The input is expected to delete the preview program from the content provider.

        The intent must contain the following bundle parameter:

        • EXTRA_PREVIEW_PROGRAM_ID: the disabled preview program ID.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_PREVIEW_PROGRAM_ADDED_TO_WATCH_NEXT
        Broadcast Action: sent by the system to tell the target TV input that one of its existing preview programs is added to the watch next programs table by user.

        The intent must contain the following bundle parameters:

        • EXTRA_PREVIEW_PROGRAM_ID: the ID of the existing preview program.
        • EXTRA_WATCH_NEXT_PROGRAM_ID: the ID of the new watch next program.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_INITIALIZE_PROGRAMS

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_INITIALIZE_PROGRAMS
        Broadcast Action: sent to the target TV input after it is first installed to notify the input to initialize its channels and programs to the system content provider.

        Note that this intent is sent only on devices with android.content.pm.PackageManager#FEATURE_LEANBACK enabled. Besides that, in order to receive this intent, the target TV input must:

        • Declare a broadcast receiver for this intent in its AndroidManifest.xml.
        • Declare appropriate permissions to write channel and program data in its AndroidManifest.xml.
        See Also:

      • METHOD_GET_COLUMNS

        public static final java.lang.String METHOD_GET_COLUMNS
        The method name to get existing columns in the given table of the specified content provider.

        The method caller must provide the following parameter:

        • arg: The content URI of the target table as a String.

        On success, the returned android.os.Bundle will include existing column names with the key EXTRA_EXISTING_COLUMN_NAMES. Otherwise, the return value will be null.

        See Also:
        ContentResolver#call(Uri, String, String, Bundle), EXTRA_EXISTING_COLUMN_NAMES, Constant Field Values

      • METHOD_ADD_COLUMN

        public static final java.lang.String METHOD_ADD_COLUMN
        The method name to add a new column in the given table of the specified content provider.

        The method caller must provide the following parameter:

        • arg: The content URI of the target table as a String.
        • extra: Name, data type, and default value of the new column in a Bundle:
          • EXTRA_COLUMN_NAME the column name as a String.
          • EXTRA_DATA_TYPE the data type as a String.
          • EXTRA_DEFAULT_VALUE the default value as a String. (optional)

        On success, the returned android.os.Bundle will include current colum names after the addition operation with the key EXTRA_EXISTING_COLUMN_NAMES. Otherwise, the return value will be null.

        See Also:
        ContentResolver#call(Uri, String, String, Bundle), EXTRA_COLUMN_NAME, EXTRA_DATA_TYPE, EXTRA_DEFAULT_VALUE, EXTRA_EXISTING_COLUMN_NAMES, Constant Field Values

      • requestChannelBrowsable

        public static void requestChannelBrowsable(Context context,
                                           long channelId)
        Requests to make a channel browsable.

        Once called, the system will review the request and make the channel browsable based on its policy. The first request from a package is guaranteed to be approved. This is only relevant to channels with TvContractCompat.Channels.TYPE_PREVIEW type.

        No-op on devices prior to android.os.Build.VERSION_CODES#O.

        Parameters:
        context - The context for accessing content provider.
        channelId - The channel ID to be browsable.
        See Also:
        TvContractCompat.Channels.COLUMN_BROWSABLE
